Anne Gerety https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Gerety 0 Anne Gerety (July 3, 1926 – October 25, 2003) was the actress who played the voice of Aunt Beru in the Star Wars radio drama.Gerety was born in New York City, and she was the sister of actor Peter Gerety. In addition to her own acting, Gerety and her husband, Tom Hill, formed the Storefront Actor's Theatre, which operated from 1970 to 1990 in Portland, Oregon.
